column232: More plain, only basic salad a bit of lettuce and cucumber and sauce, for adults I do more varied salad including onions, tomato and salsa sauce.
column234: Choosing vegetables the children will eat so carrots, broccoli, sweetcorn. For just adults I would mix the veg up a bit more but the meat is the same.
column236: No change everyone has it the same I don't make changes, I serve it with frozen veg often so it's just the basics but I would do the same for adults.
column238: I keep the filling simple just meat and veg with a simple gravy filling, I think for just adults I'd do more spicy fillings like curry.
column239: I would serve the same for everyone with no changes, filling would be something the children do like, beans are a favourite in our house.
column240: The children love dumplings so I always include these to make sure they eat the whole dish, I feel the same so would do exactly the same for adults.
column243: One of my children is allergic to dairy so we all eat dairy free pizza when eating together. The children like simple cheese and tomato or pepperoni, For the adults I also add jalapenos.
column245: We all eat the same tasty but not too adventurous, if I was only cooking for adults I would add more spice to the sauce.
column246: Again keep it simple for the children nice flavours but not too much seasoning. For only adults I would add jalapenos
column247: For children a simple tomato based sauce and nothing too fancy with the filling. For adults I would opt more for goats cheese and strong flavours the children wouldn't like.
column249: A simple sauce goes down well with children, for adults I'd add more vegetables to the sauce and more spice.
column250: Keep it mild for the children, I normally serve adults then pour in loads of dairy free cream for the children.
column252: I keep the ingredients to food I know the children like just chicken and simple veg. For adults I'd add extra garlic and prawns which the children would refuse to eat.
column258: The meal kits are really popular in our house so I stick with these and every one will eat them. For adults maybe a bit more spice but the same otherwise.
column259: I don't put too much meat in as the children don't like too much, so more veg. I would have more chilli in adults.
column260: Again the meal kits are enjoyed by the children, they really like refried beans so I use these
column261: I use prepared from Tesco because the children like this version. I like it for the the adults too so no different.
